file=Product/loom/operational/commands/loom-commands.md · tb=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| "what are we assuming", "riskiest assumption", "leap of faith", "what could kill this" \| assumption-mapping \| /assume \| · tb=\| "run an experiment", "test this", "A/B", "fake door", "decision rule", "freeze criteria" \| experiment-discipline \| /experiment \| · tb=\| "have we tested this", "experiment history", "record the verdict", "did we try that" \| experiment-registry \| /registry \| · tb=\| "do we have PMF", "product-market fit", "Ellis survey", "retention curve", "double down or pivot" \| pmf-scorecard \| /pmf \| · p:Precedence=1. A proposed experiment queries experiment-registry FIRST — re-running a settled test needs a stated delta.\n2. experiment-discipline will not run until metric (experiment-instrumentation) reports instruments verified-live.\n3. PMF verdicts route to spec/marcus as evidence — the double-down/pivot decision is theirs, not loom's.\n4. Criteria/decision-rule freeze precedes data always; a post-hoc success bar bounces.\n